2. Backend Technologies
Language & Framework: JavaScript via Node.js and Express.js.

Testing: Jest (for unit testing and coverage reports).

Justification & Design Support: We chose Node.js and Express because their asynchronous, event-driven architecture is highly efficient at handling concurrent API requests, which is critical for a real-time queue management system where multiple users may be joining or checking status simultaneously. By keeping both our frontend (React) and backend (Node) in JavaScript, we ensured seamless data serialization and integration. For testing, Jest was selected because of its built-in coverage reporting and fast execution, allowing us to rigorously isolate and validate our mathematical wait-time estimation models and API validation logic without needing a persistent database.

